Kernel-isolation B: k=1 (no polyphase, L=3000, pk) with k=5's small kernels (13, 3, 4) instead of the apr24/apr26 baseline (63, 15, 15). RF = 125 raw-ms (vs baseline 623 raw-ms — much shorter context, matching apr25 k=5 in raw-ms). Default channels (64/128/256). Tests whether full-resolution input rescues a small-kernel model. R² near +0.30+ → polyphase rate also matters and the architectural argument is incomplete. R² near +0.10 (matching apr25 k=5 +0.087) → kernel architecture alone explains the gap regardless of input rate.